whereas.text:
Whereas Sikhism is the fifth largest world religion with approximately 25,000,000 adherents from
			 diverse backgrounds throughout the world, including 500,000 adherents in
			 the United States;

Whereas Sikhs in the United States pursue diverse professions and walks of life, making rich
			 contributions to the economic vibrancy of the United States as farmers,
			 engineers, doctors, scientists, and business owners;

Whereas Vaisakhi is one of the most religiously significant days in Sikh history, commemorating the
			 creation of the Khalsa, a fellowship of devout Sikhs, by Guru Gobind Singh
			 in 1699;
